<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - DETROIT DIESEL SERIES 60 ENGINE - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL (TPS/IVS) - DETROIT DIESEL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ACCELERATOR PEDAL (TPS/IVS) - DETROIT DIESEL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Review the circuit diagram and inspect the TPS circuits and connectors as outlined in
                <hotlnk document="s08270_166.xml" xrefid="x0827801">Before Troubleshooting</hotlnk>. The following 3
                tests,
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0827802">Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) - Detroit Diesel</hotlnk>,
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0827803">Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS) - Detroit Diesel</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0827804">Testing Accelerator Pedal (TPS/IVS) Circuits - Detroit Diesel</hotlnk>, check
                the TPS/IVS connection and related International cab and engine harness connections leading to the ECM.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following 3 tests must be performed in sequence.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x0827802">
            <title>Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) - Detroit Diesel</title>
            <para>This test checks the TPS circuits in the accelerator pedal assembly. This test will identify if the
                resistance of the pedal circuits is within specifications.
            </para>
            <table id="t0827801" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) - Detroit Diesel</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.85in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="1.08in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.02in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect the accelerator pedal from cab harness connector (306). At the pedal
                                    side of (306) measure resistance between terminals A and C with the pedal in the
                                    idle position, then with the pedal fully depressed. Resistance should be 2000 to
                                    3000 ohms in all positions.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At accelerator pedal (306), A to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2000 to 3000 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Replace TPS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With the pedal at idle, at connector (306) measure resistance between terminals B
                                    and C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At accelerator pedal (306), B to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>1500 to 3000 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace TPS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With pedal at full throttle position, at connector (306) measure resistance
                                    between terminals B and C. Resistance must be 1000 ohms less than reading at idle
                                    position and must be 250 to 1500 ohms.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At accelerator pedal (306), B to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>250 to 1500 ohms, and 1000 less than idle position reading.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace TPS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At accelerator pedal, measure resistance to the metal part of pedal assembly and
                                    terminals A, B, C, D and E.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Accelerator pedal (306), metal to terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>TPS sensor checks good. Go to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0827803">Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS)- Detroit Diesel.
                                    </hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace TPS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0827803">
            <title>Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS) - Detroit Diesel</title>
            <para>Perform preceding test before performing this test. This test checks the IVS circuits in the
                accelerator pedal assembly.
            </para>
            <table id="t0827802" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS) - Detroit Diesel</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.74in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="1.11in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.16in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With accelerator pedal still disconnected at connector (306) and the pedal at
                                    idle, measure resistance between terminal F and E on the accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At accelerator pedal (306) , F to E.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60; 125 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace TPS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (306), measure resistance between terminals E and F while slowly
                                    depressing the pedal (idle to full throttle). After approximately 10&#176; of travel
                                    the resistance should be 100K ohms or more.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At accelerator pedal (306), E to F, after 10&#176; of travel.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace TPS/IVS sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>The TPS and IVS functions check good.
                                    <emph type="bold">NOTE: This test is not able to check the timing function between
                                        the two functions.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0827804">Testing Accelerator Pedal (TPS/IVS) Circuits - Detroit
                                        Diesel
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    following.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0827804">
            <title>Testing Accelerator Pedal (TPS/IVS) Circuits - Detroit Diesel</title>
            <para>Inspect TPS/IVS circuits and connectors as outlined in
                <hotlnk document="s08270_166.xml" xrefid="x0827801">Before Troubleshooting</hotlnk>. This test checks
                the cab and engine harness TPS/IVS circuits for opens, shorts to ground, shorts to "hot" circuits and
                shorts to other circuits in the harness and checks the circuits for continuity.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Perform the two preceding tests before performing this test.</emph>
            </para>
            <table id="t0827803" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Accelerator Pedal (TPS/IVS) Circuits - Detroit Diesel</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.74in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.40in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With accelerator pedal disconnected from the cab harness at (306), disconnect
                                    connector (341) from the ECM. At International ECM connector (341), measure
                                    resistance to ground at terminals E1, C3, D2 and A3 [circuits 99B, 99-R, 99 and
                                    99A(5V)].
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), term. E1, C3, D2 and A3 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit where resistance at terminal is less than 100K
                                    ohms, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) measure resistance between terminals E1, C3, D2, A3 [circuits
                                    99B, 99-R, 99 and 99A(5V)] and all other terminals in connector (341).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), term. E1, C3, D2 and A3, and all other term.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short between circuits where resistance between terminals is less than 100K
                                    ohms, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) measure voltage to ground at terminals E1, C3, D2, A3 [circuits
                                    99B, 99-R, 99 and 99A(5V)].
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), term. E1, C3, D2 and A3 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60; 1 volt.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to unwanted voltage source in circuit with more than 1V, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (306) measure resistance to ground at terminal F (circuit 99-GA).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(306), F to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99-GA, 97-GA, 97-G, or 11-G to negative
                                    battery terminal, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) use test lead to jumper terminal E1 (circuit 99B) to ground. At
                                    connector (306) measure resistance between terminals E and F (circuits 99B and
                                    99-GA).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(306), E to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99B between connectors (341) and (306),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) use test lead to jumper terminal C3 (circuit 99-R) to ground.
                                    At connector (306) measure resistance between terminals A and F (cir. 99R and
                                    99-GA).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(306), A to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99-R between connectors (341) and (306),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) use test lead to jumper terminal D2 (cir. 99) to ground. At
                                    connector (306) measure resistance between terminals B and F (cir. 99 and 99-GA).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(306), B to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99 between connectors (341) and (306),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) use test lead to jumper terminal A3 [cir. 99A(5V)] to ground.
                                    At connector (306) measure resistance between terminals C and F [cir. 99A(5V) and
                                    99-GA].
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(306), C to F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>TPS/ IVS circuits between (341) and (306) check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99A between connectors (341) and (306),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
